---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import NewsletterCTA from '../components/NewsletterCTA.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description={`What ${SITE.name} is, who writes it, and the promise behind every recommendation and guide.`}
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-10 sm:px-6">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'About' }]} />
    <article class="prose prose-lg mt-6 max-w-none">
      <h1>About {SITE.name}</h1>
      <p>
        {SITE.name} is a small, independent site about <strong>cozy and simulation games</strong> —
        the relaxing, low-stress kind you play to unwind: farming sims, life sims, gentle
        building and management games, and everything in the same warm, wholesome corner.
      </p>
      <p>
        Cozy games are having a moment, and there are more of them than ever. That's wonderful —
        and a little overwhelming. Our job is to help you cut through the noise: to find a game
        worth your evening, decide whether it's worth your money, and get unstuck when you need a hand.
      </p>

      <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Recommendations</strong> — curated lists by platform, mood, and budget ("games like Stardew Valley," "best cozy games on Switch").</li>
        <li><strong>Reviews</strong> — honest, spoiler-light takes on whether a game is worth it.</li>
        <li><strong>Guides</strong> — beginner-friendly tips so you spend less time stuck and more time relaxing.</li>
        <li><strong>Resources</strong> — mods, gift guides, and cozy gear round-ups.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Who's behind it</h2>
      <p>
        {SITE.name} is written by people who genuinely love this genre and have spent an
        embarrassing number of hours in these little towns and valleys. We play the games we
        write about and aim to give the kind of practical, friendly advice we'd give a friend.
      </p>

      <h2>Our promise</h2>
      <p>
        Recommendations are based on the actual experience of playing — never on who pays the most.
        Some links on this site are affiliate links, which means we may earn a small commission if
        you buy through them, at no extra cost to you. That support helps keep the site running, but
        it never changes our honest opinion. You can read the full
        <a href="/disclosure">affiliate disclosure</a> any time.
      </p>
      <p>Spotted something out of date or have a game we should cover? <a href="/contact">Get in touch</a> — we'd love to hear from you.</p>
    </article>

    <NewsletterCTA class="mt-12" />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
